{
  "signal_description": "The query retrieves various metrics related to invoice processing. It selects the following columns from the 'defaultview-529' table: 'Inv. Company Code Text', 'Inv. Converted USD Amount', 'case_id', 'Dunning Block Rate', 'Inv. Accounting Document Number', 'Last Inv. Item Due Date', 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date', 'Inv. Posting Document Date', 'Event Created By User Type', and 'event_name'. It then calculates the sum of 'Inv. Converted USD Amount' as 'Invoice Amount in $', the count of 'case_id' as 'No. of Invoices', the average of 'Dunning Block Rate' as 'Ø Dunning Block Rate in %', the average of the time difference between 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' and 'Inv. Posting Document Date' as 'Ø Days Posting to Net Due Date', the percentage of invoices with 'Event Created By User Type' matching 'System' and 'event_name' matching 'Post Invoice' as 'Automatic Invoice Posting in %', the percentage of invoices with multiple occurrences of 'event_name' not equal to 'Create Goods Receipt' as 'Rework Rate in %', the percentage of invoices with 'event_name' matching '%change%' as 'Change Rate in %', the percentage of invoices with 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' less than 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date' as 'Late Payment Rate in %', the average of 'Dunning Block Duration' as 'Ø Dunning Block Duration in Days', and the average of the time difference between the last occurrence of 'END_TIME' where 'EVENT_NAME' is 'Remove Dunning Block' and the first occurrence of 'END_TIME' where 'EVENT_NAME' is 'Post Invoice' as 'Ø Total Cycle Time'. The results are grouped by 'Inv. Company Code Text' and ordered by 'Invoice Amount in $' in descending order."
}
